  "text": "In this study, we found a considerable number of differentially regulated miRNA in the cancer tissue compared with the controls. Although a number of the former has been identified in other profile studies, a large fraction has not been described in head and neck cancer before. In the comprehensive profile study of 51 tumour samples of the oral cavity, pharynx and larynx by [CITATION_1] , only 10 miRNAs (miR-93, miR-25, miR-155, miR-21, miR-let7i, miR-223, miR-99a, miR100, miR-125b, miR-375) from a total of 322 examined miRNAs were identical to the ones found in this study.",
